Los robots matan
Cuando hablamos de robots, nos acordamos de Asimov y de sus <a href="http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tres_leyes_de_la_rob%C3%B3tica">leyes de la robótica</a>. El caso es que, naturalmente, estamos lejos de que esas leyes puedan incluirse en el conjunto de leyes de un robot normal y sin embargo, cada vez <a href="http://www.tecnologia.carrefour.es/home_roomba.asp">los tenemos mas cerca</a> (venden el Roomba en el Carrefour, quien imaginaba eso, hace no tanto?).

De esas cosas hablan en <a href="http://www.economist.com/PrinterFriendly.cfm?story_id=7001829&CFID=6451287&CFTOKEN=13937510">Trust me, I'm a robot</a>.

<blockquote>
Indeed, despite the introduction of improved safety mechanisms, robots have claimed many more victims since 1981. Over the years people have been crushed, hit on the head, welded and even had molten aluminium poured over them by robots. Last year there were 77 robot-related accidents in Britain alone, according to the Health and Safety Executive.
</blockquote>


